N. essay, trial, endeavor, attempt
aim, struggle, venture, adventure, speculation, coup d'essai [Fr.], debut
probation &c. (experiment). V. try, essay
experiment &c.
endeavor, strive
tempt, attempt, make an attempt
venture, adventure, speculate, take one's chance, tempt fortune
try one's fortune, try one's luck, try one's hand
use one's endeavor
feel one's way, grope one's way, pick one's way. try hard, push, make a bold push, use one's best endeavor
do one's best &c. (exertion). Adj. essaying &c. v.
experimental &c.
tentative, empirical, probationary. experimentally &c. adj.
on trial, at a venture
by rule of thumb. if one may be so bold. aut non tentaris aut perfice [Lat.] [Ovid]
chi non s'arrischia non guadagna [Fr.].
